23/12/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis met with Albanian counterpart Sali Berisha in Athens on Thursday (22 December) to discuss prospects for co-operation and outstanding bilateral issues.
They vowed to intensify co-operation and boost efforts against organised crime and corruption.
They also discussed ways to encourage Greek investments in Albania as well as possible co-operation in education.
(Albanian News - 23/12/05)
